For a chain restaurant Blaze Pizza has got one of the best recipes for success in customer satisfaction that I've seen.  You can select anything you want on the build your own individual sized thin crust pizza at a reasonable price. The crust (also available in gluten free) is super thin and crispy the way I prefer it, and it's ready in minutes in the fire oven after selecting all the ingredients for the topping. I especially love the extras you can add after it comes out of the oven.  I usually add a pesto glaze and fresh arugula to mine.  And all this for around $11.  The seating area has a nice industrial vibe to it.  The specialty juices in addition to the standard soft drinks are also a nice touch.

Blaze Pizza is a build your own pizza place with an assembly line format. It is fun, simple, and quick! The service at this blaze is great, and the staff is very attentive if you need something. The portions you receive for the price are excellent and the toppings are unlimited. There are options for every type of eater!  Vegan options- let the staff know right away you have a vegan order and they will change their gloves. They even have vegan cheese! I love the spicy red sauce, and get nearly every veggie they have on my pizza. They will always ask you if your pizza looks good to you before putting it in the oven, which I think is a nice touch. Veggies have a lot of liquid and can sometimes make the pizza soggy if you put too many- so I always get mine extra toasted to make sure I have a crispy bottom.  Meat eaters- the meat toppings are still unlimited and they have a wide variety! You can also get traditional pizzas or select from the combos they have on the menu.  Highly recommend for the area

Blaze Pizza on Clinton Street is an establishment in the heart of downtown Chicago. It offers Customize-able, quick, healthy pizza for under $8.00 and is a great deal. The staff is friendly, courteous and does their best to meet needs of the consumer. The dough is made fresh daily. There are gluten free and vegan options .There is a wide variety of toppings available, and you can see the pizza being prepared right in front of you in their brick oven. The lines at times may seem long, however it certainly does not feel like it. Blaze offers a choice of two salads, cold drinks and teas, along with a choice of alcohol for your palate. They offer dine and carry out. In the summer, there is a patio and umbrellas to provide shade for outside dining. I highly recommend Blaze Pizza and look forward to going back soon.
